### Detect Empty State in Payload CMS Lexical Rich Text Editor Data

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/rich-text/overview.mdx

This utility function, `hasText` from `@payloadcms/richtext-lexical/shared`, helps determine if a rich text field's data contains actual text. This is crucial because an empty rich text editor might store an empty JSON object instead of `null`, making a simple null check insufficient. It takes the rich text data as an argument and returns a boolean indicating the presence of text.

```TypeScript
import { hasText } from '@payloadcms/richtext-lexical/shared'

hasText(richtextData)
```
